$ python my_program.py --quotes hello "\"world\""
{'"': 2, ' ': 1, 'd': 1, 'e': 1, 'h': 1, 'l': 3, 'o': 2, 'r': 1, 'w': 1}
```

In the above examples, the first command counts the characters in the string `"hello world"` without including quotes. The second command counts the characters in the string `"hello "world" --quotes"`, including quotes. The third command has the same input string as the second example, but uses a different ordering of command line arguments to get the same result.
